I am trying to follow the instructions for building the latest Cantera
source in Win32 using VC7.  I am getting errors trying to buld the
code in the python section.  

In the ctpython, custom build when c:/python23/python.exe winsetup.py
build (or install) is run I get many errors.  Below are a sample of
the error messages.  The final error is "unresolved externals".

I'm not familiar with python, and am only trying to build the minimal
needed to get the Cantera-Matlab interface working.

I know I was able to get this part to build in the past week or two,
but have tinkered with my system and have run cvs update on my cantera
dir.  I guess it can't find something it needs. Any thoughts on what
is missing and how I can help the linker find it? 

Many thanks in advance

BTW C:\Python23\PCBuild does not exist on my system, but I'm not sure
where the build command is getting this from.
